    "solution": "<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 23rd January Evening Shift Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 13 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mldforiw/fff3b7ff-1782-41ea-9b58-ddd0bc254f34/7c9ded80-04c1-11f1-bcf3-d9d8377c520a/file-6y3zli1mldforix.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mldforiw/fff3b7ff-1782-41ea-9b58-ddd0bc254f34/7c9ded80-04c1-11f1-bcf3-d9d8377c520a/file-6y3zli1mldforix.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>Molecular mass of compound $Q$ is $157$.</p>\n<p>In $Q$, oxygen contributes mass $16$ (for one oxygen atom).</p>\n<p>So, percentage of oxygen in $Q$ is $$\\% \\text{ of oxygen in product ' } Q \\text{ ' is }=\\frac{16}{157} \\times 100=10.19 \\%$$</p>\n<p>Nearest integer $=10$%.</p>",
